Frighten

With this spell, the druid can cause a primal,
unreasoning fear to arise in any natural creature
native to this world.  Unlike most of a druid's
emotion-influencing powers, this spell works on
humanoids as well as animals and plants.  However,
elementals, demons, undead, and other unnatural
creatures are immune.

Command: frighten <target> (defaults to attacker)
Base Cost: 25 SP
Base Recovery: fast
Base Effect: target flees
Base Duration: instant
Guild Level: 5
